>
> If its not DMI then what is the protocol for analogue vga for monitor
> control and discovery?  Anyhow I meant analogue if it has the control
> bus :)
>   
I think that DMI gives informations on your hardware, like, on my
laptop, serial number, RAM serial number, etc... But nothing on the
monitors (at least not on my laptop).

The protocol that discover monitors is DDC (supported resolutions,
refresh rates, etc...), and the protocol that controls the monitor is
DDC/CI.

Best regards,

Nicolas
